# SEO conventions

Google Search Console flags missing meta descriptions and anchors without crawlable `href` values. Follow these rules on every public page and shared chrome change.

## Meta description

- **Full pages** rendered with [components/head.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/head.html) MUST pass `seo=seo` from the endpoint (or hub service) using [SeoService](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/seo/SeoService.java).
- **Indexable pages** (`noindex == false`) MUST have a non-blank `SeoMetadata.description()` — add a fallback in `SeoService` when source text is empty (see `forBlogHome`, `forAuthorProfile`, `forPost`).
- **Error pages** use `SeoService.forError(status)` via [GenericExceptionMapper](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/infra/GenericExceptionMapper.java).
- **Private / hub pages** use `SeoService.forPrivatePage(...)` (includes description + `noindex`).
- Do not add a second `<meta name="description">` outside [components/seo-meta-tags.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/seo-meta-tags.html).

## Crawlable links

Every `<a>` that navigates via HTMX MUST include a real **`href`** matching the navigation target:

```html
<a href="{post.url}"
   data-hx-get="{post.url}"
   hx-select="main"
   hx-target="main"
   hx-push-url="{post.url}">…</a>
```

- Put `href` on the same element as `data-hx-get` / `hx-get` (or `hx-push-url` when that is the canonical URL).
- **Shared chrome** ([header.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/header.html), [footer.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/footer.html), [breadcrumb.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/breadcrumb.html)) affects every page — fix these first.
- Modal-only triggers may keep `href="#"` when they do not navigate (login/signup modals). Do not use `#` for real routes.

Reference pattern: [blog-directory-card.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/blog-directory-card.html).

## HTMX SEO refresh

After in-app navigation, [SeoComponentEndpoint](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/seo/SeoComponentEndpoint.java) updates `#seo-head` and `#page-title` via OOB swap. New public routes must be mappable in `SeoService.resolveFromPath`.

## Verification

Before finishing template or SEO changes:

```bash
scripts/audit-template-seo.sh
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=SeoServiceTest,SeoWebTest
```

Extend `SeoServiceTest` / `SeoWebTest` when adding new public routes or head rendering paths.
